dcterms:description: A rich administrative dataset from the annuity market in Chile, structured as first-price auctions followed by bargaining between retirees and firms, containing demographic characteristics, savings, pension offers, and mortality data.
dcterms:title: Administrative dataset from the annuity market in Chile

dcterms:description: A centralized electronic platform for annuities in Chile that facilitates the auction process for retirees seeking annuity offers from various firms.
dcterms:title: SCOMP (centralized electronic platform for annuities in Chile)

dcterms:description: Mortality data for retirees used to estimate expected longevity and inform the annuity pricing and offers.
dcterms:title: Mortality data for retirees

dcterms:creator: U.S. GAO
dcterms:description: Data from the Centers for Medicare and Medicaid Services (CMS) related to competitive bidding programs for durable medical equipment and diabetes testing supplies.
dcterms:title: Data from the Centers for Medicare and Medicaid Services (CMS)

dcterms:description: Data from the Chilean pension system that provides insights into the structure and performance of the pension market.
dcterms:title: Data from the Chilean pension system

dcterms:description: Data from the TIAA Institute that provides research and insights into retirement and financial security.
dcterms:title: Data from the TIAA Institute

dcterms:creator: Roberto Rocha
Craig Thorburn
dcterms:description: Data from the World Bank that discusses the development of annuities markets, particularly focusing on the experience of Chile.
